* Example string:  myString = "What A Great Dog!" *

* Length of a string:  myString.length*

* Find first char in string:  myString[0]  or myString[12]   // Ensure people know which character they want:  "First" is NOT "Zeroth" *

* Find LAST char in string:  myString[myString.length - 1];
* Find the Nth-to-Last char in string:  myString[myString.length - N]; <--Where N is any number < the number of chars in myString






